# YAML Configuration Standards

## File Formatting Rules

### Array Spacing
- No spaces after opening bracket or before closing bracket
- ✅ CORRECT: `[main, develop]` or `["item1", "item2"]`
- ❌ WRONG: `[ main, develop ]` or `[ "item1", "item2" ]`

### File Endings
- YAML files MUST end with exactly one newline
- No trailing blank lines beyond the final content line
- Verify with: `yamllint <file>`

### Duplicate Prevention
- In `.pre-commit-config.yaml`: Each hook ID must appear only once
- In `labeler.yml`: Avoid redundant path specifications (use globs instead of explicit + glob)
- In `dependabot.yml`: No duplicate package ecosystems with same directory

## Pre-commit Hook Configuration

When adding hooks to `.pre-commit-config.yaml`:
1. Check if hook ID already exists before adding
2. Group related hooks together
3. Use consistent indentation (2 spaces)
4. Verify with: `pre-commit run --all-files`

## Configuration Validation

Before committing YAML changes:
```bash
yamllint .github/workflows/*.yml
yamllint .github/*.yml
yamllint .pre-commit-config.yaml
```
